Amended JOC reflects 06-24-15 Court order commuting Probation term on Count 1 to one year.
NOTE:  Assessment due dates have been changed to reflect the order
Order Commuting Probation Term, signed and filed.
Per Order of the Presiding Judge, Misdemeanor Division, the motion/request is hereby assigned to Reserve Br. 45, for review. mag
DOC request to clarify length of probation term.

Defendant James H Aschenbrenner in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    
Defendant ordered to serve 30 days in the House of Correction with credit of 1 day time served, and with Huber Privileges for work and school.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation with the Mental Health Unit for 18 months with the following conditions:
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Maintain absolute sobriety.  No illegal drugs.
*Mental Health evaluation.
*Obtain high school diplom or GED.
*Obatin employment within 60 days..
*Defendant to pay all costs and surcharges during period of probation at a rate of $25.00 monthly, commencing 07-10-2015, and the 1st of each month thereafter. If unpaid a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant.
